[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring command execution**\n\nI'm working with the executeTag function, which returns the command line from the tag command only if it runs successfully. I could assert that it contains the string \"tag --no-sign -F\", but I'm curious about potential differences in command line quoting. Additionally, when using git ls-files in an empty repository with a committed list of tracked paths, I need to ensure I'm returning only the tagged files. Setting up an actual git repository without a network might be necessary, and I wonder if I could use the existing tests as a process helper.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_095fba92254ac1e9016a2a2da8a8f081908aa942b82fdf0d04\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKi2tqcZ4DGJU9PVwI2Fer6yHiZanPLtIXLI83NCd2ieWVd9T1gTgnoOGiKh1MY-y02chRO4pO1McBovPq0rKzq9RqKPx9Ia1XByZWTa-02Wg2nQQ6RFkOWSMFu9VZR4xf7lHkVRIdL2-zxZTiPYIhNSNnghts4hYcKvZByx_7ePoV_Jvt6q4ppNxMoG_49sgM4vbR8j8KXq-C-71_7-m7B4-0MkxE7Sp0NpqNoT8BdWzHAd5x4T-OIAJgOg-RzlRoylJVIobTYhMHA2u9AN_OpHV72FpZ47Noym9Py_QN2ajA8ytA6iIcT_37xu22x_KPUju102siqh-0NJ1l_JCI19KWSqDEFu01MDW9JibYWAa1-V-M8hHMcB4wjBwy6t_-nxVBc1Y7N3k1-UMyYTyWres9limu9Q7c-Bvu7vtkplciUfszlLWjeCnz6RJQMJUyo1JM72zTW4K92DGM6gyA_XP8taMd8hVEQGrTpy4-0tLXDZTbyDjBu2MRgssHELyPhviJ8cUpK78t9-fQh9bZ52VlWBA5vC2njOT-DVoUb31oq9aVHoX7mnnwfG2ibXh0NG1uAvTl7C6RY7wWTTJVrp3rtRr0ENIXeXR9ToPwndcHpOjLMQPDMm4-skPacCMCgOWNub4Ac6j3wIpP9kZce3-vgX0MdxthY8XvI4WG05QoNMP-iiWjYAO9fzNEyXhXDoEJkfZLhdeFDGBYZBo6yAoqPNi1VQeyu8Ucp7Ksq0DL75xFjBMjo6Trjof7EJgcVgVljLfVr9QFyC1rYV06MtkuJ307GGnPWa3xM4rMSqAPQiu2ywlR2C3Mw6W7inRZdgA9O44EiWrkqburWdvwm-ZnIhx1sNvNJ1jHL3FOu0x2aKdePBhwNcXxvh5EcRmluzrCokCzjta1mAiW1NExTO90PN2nPLmuErGB0dY0jhlb4Mp4wOOYe7CPFVbs-GteiwrU6oRwS93obU_SR-_8uhbphcu71J9XPFvinHn4hihKtF0aPGJ7Fqvx-OGo4x_HkGyXTaim81j2vBOwML27rF3UEvWbobBZ_2QlDCz7nQDEOeArP8Zci_0AeSYScIn5krVesB010iiJS5QCPdsOUe7OtgV6nn4mMG9rKmwu8qj3KLQN2mQqZA