will fail, which is concerning. However, I wonder if the CI image includes git—likely, it does. To minimize dependencies, though, I think I could use the public `executeTagCommand` since there aren’t really alternatives. \\n\\nHmm, I considered making a nested subclass for tests, but that doesn't seem right. I’ll need to use `executeTagCommand` instead of direct calls, focusing on keeping signed coverage while ensuring arguments include `--no-sign`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing tag command execution**\\n\\nI'm thinking the default behavior has no sign in older versions, and perhaps I don't need a separate branch for signed dynamic calls since the initial test already covers the signed tag branch. But with the new API, the FORCE_SIGN branch can't run without gpg, and accessing the direct factory isn’t possible. I might leave that untested since the task is mainly focused on fixes. However, using FORCE_NO_SIGN for tag command execution should cover the changes and test the new supported behavior.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_l7WSzizcH1f0EF8dvBVwyDJD|fc_095fba92254ac1e9016a2a2dcb7a64819093991da580511cdb", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/2.2.1/src/test/java/org_apache_maven_scm/maven_scm_provider_gitexe/GitExeCommandLineConstructionTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;", "newText": "import java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;"}, {"oldText": "import org.apache.maven.scm.ScmException;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.ScmFileSet;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.ScmTag;", "newText": "import org.apache.maven.scm.ScmException;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.ScmFileSet;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.ScmResult;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.ScmTag;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.ScmTagParameters;"}, {"oldText": "import org.apache.maven.scm.command.info.InfoItem;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.provider.ScmProviderRepository;", "newText": "import org.apache.maven.scm.command.info.InfoItem;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.command.tag.TagScmResult;\nimport org.apache.maven.scm.provider.ScmProviderRepository;"}, {"oldText": "        GitScmProviderRepository repository = new GitScmProviderRepository(\"https://example.invalid/team/project.git\");\n        ScmTag startTag = new ScmTag(\"v1.0.0\");", "newText": "        GitScmProviderRepository repository = new GitScmProviderRepository(\"https://example.invalid/team/project.git\");\n        repository.setPushChanges(false);\n        ScmTag startTag = new ScmTag(\"v1.0.0\");"}, {"oldText": "        Commandline tagCommandLine = GitTagCommand.createCommandLine(\n                repository, workingDirectory, \"v1.1.0\", messagePath.toFile(), SignOption.DEFAULT);\n        assertThat(tagCommandLine.getArguments())\n                .containsExactly(\"tag\", \"-F\", messagePath.toAbsolutePath().toString(), \"v1.1.0\");\n\n        Commandline signedTagCommandLine = GitTagCommand.createCommandLine(\n                repository, workingDirectory, \"v1.1.0\", messagePath.toFile(), SignOption.FORCE_SIGN);\n        assertThat(signedTagCommandLine.getArguments())\n                .containsExactly(\"tag\", \"-s\", \"-F\", messagePath.toAbsolutePath().toString(), \"v1.1.0\");\n\n        Commandline unsignedTagCommandLine = GitTagCommand.createCommandLine(\n                repository, workingDirectory, \"v1.1.0\", messagePath.toFile(), SignOption.FORCE_NO_SIGN);\n        assertThat(unsignedTagCommandLine.getArguments())\n                .containsExactly(\"tag\", \"--no-sign\", \"-F\", messagePath.toAbsolutePath().toString(), \"v1.1.0\");\n\n        Commandline tagPushCommandLine = new GitTagCommand(Map.of()).createPushCommandLine(\n                repository, new ScmFileSet(workingDirectory, trackedPath.toFile()), \"v1.1.0\");", "newText": "        initializeGitRepository(workingDirectory);\n        ScmTagParameters tagParameters = new ScmTagParameters(\"release message\");\n        tagParameters.setSignOption(SignOption.FORCE_NO_SIGN);\n        ScmResult tagResult = new GitTagCommand(Map.of())\n                .executeTagCommand(repository, new ScmFileSet(workingDirectory), \"v1.1.0\", tagParameters);\n        assertThat(tagResult.isSuccess()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(tagResult.getCommandLine()).contains(\"tag\", \"--no-sign\", \"-F\", \"v1.1.0\");\n        TagScmResult tagScmResult = (TagScmResult) tagResult;\n        assertThat(tagScmResult.getTaggedFiles()).isNotEmpty();\n\n        Commandline tagPushCommandLine = new GitTagCommand(Map.of()).createPushCommandLine(\n                repository, new ScmFileSet(workingDirectory, trackedPath.toFile()), \"v1.1.0\");"}, {"oldText": "    private static void assertGitExecutable(Commandline commandLine) {\n        assertThat(commandLine.getExecutable()).isIn(\"git\", \"'git'\");\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static void assertGitExecutable(Commandline commandLine) {\n        assertThat(commandLine.getExecutable()).isIn(\"git\", \"'git'\");\n    }\n\n    private static void initializeGitRepository(File workingDirectory) throws Exception {\n        runGitCommand(workingDirectory, \"init\");\n        runGitCommand(workingDirectory, \"config\", \"user.email\", \"native-tests@example.invalid\");\n        runGitCommand(workingDirectory, \"config\", \"user.name\", \"Native Tests\");\n        runGitCommand(workingDirectory, \"add\", \"tracked.txt\");\n        runGitCommand(workingDirectory, \"commit\", \"-m\", \"initial commit\");\n    }\n\n    private static void runGitCommand(File workingDirectory, String... arguments) throws Exception {\n        String[] command = new String[arguments.length + 1];\n        command[0] = \"git\";\n        System.arraycopy(arguments, 0, command, 1, arguments.length);\n\n        Process process = new ProcessBuilder(command)\n                .directory(workingDirectory)\n                .redirectErrorStream(true)\n                .start();\n        boolean completed = process.waitFor(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS);\n        String output = new String(process.getInputStream().readAllBytes(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n        if (!completed) {\n            process.destroyForcibly();\n        }\n        assertThat(completed).as(\"git command timed out: %s\", String.join(\" \", command)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(process.exitValue()).as(output).isZero();\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 9399, "output": 2589, "cacheRead": 19456, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31444, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781149101950, "responseId": "resp_095fba92254ac1e9016a2a2daeb0f88190a25859e7788516f8"}}
